{
  "texts": [
    "PubLayNet [49] is the first dataset of this type, counting 500k annotated PDF pages, and leveraging automatic annotation techniques.",
    "Following this thread, even larger datasets have been developed, looking for even more classes.",
    "Today, these datasets allow researchers to obtain the best results in DLA.",
    "PubLayNetPubLayNet [49] has been developed aiming to construct a dataset to be the largest ever created for DLA.",
    "PubLayNet is made up of publicly available scientific journals, specifically medical ones, in PDF and XML format, taken from PMC and labeled as described in Sect. 3.2.2 using PDFMiner [39].Layout categories have been chosen to cover important document regions, such as paragraphs, titles, lists, images, and tables."
  ]
}